articles.headline: Hurts, Eagles get last word on Chiefs in Super Bowl rematch
articles.description: The Eagles got the final word during a hotly contested Super Bowl rematch with the Chiefs on Sunday that was intense to the very end.

articles.headline: Arizona Cardinals fend off Carolina Panthers for 2-0 start
articles.description: A week after surviving a late-game push by New Orleans Saints, the Arizona Cardinals had to pull off a similar feat Sunday in their home opener against the Panthers, holding off Carolina 27-22 after racing out to 27-3 lead early in the third quarter.

images.name: Cardinals' scoop and score
images.caption: Josh Sweat forces fumble and Zaven Collins recovers for the Cardinals TD.

articles.headline: Sources: Bengals' Joe Burrow may need surgery for turf toe
articles.description: Cincinnati Bengals star quarterback Joe Burrow is dealing with a turf toe injury that could require surgery, sources told ESPN's Adam Schefter on Sunday night.

articles.headline: Lions make point against Ben Johnson, Bears with 52-21 rout
articles.description: In a game they called "personal," the Lions scored 52 points on former offensive coordinator Ben Johnson, whose Bears dropped to 0-2 in his first season.

images.name: Ben Johnson/Dan Campbell [600x600]
images.caption: Ben Johnson, left, and Dan Campbell embrace after Sunday's game, the first between the two since Johnson left his offensive coordinator job in Detroit to be Chicago's head coach.

articles.headline: Falcons-Vikings NFL Week 2 highlights
articles.description: J.J. McCarthy's 50-yard pass to Justin Jefferson sets up Will Reichard for a 51-yard FG just before halftime.

articles.headline: Sources: Clowney deal with Cowboys for 1 year, up to $6M
articles.description: The Cowboys have signed three-time Pro Bowl edge rusher Jadeveon Clowney to a contract, owner Jerry Jones said after the team's overtime win against the Giants on Sunday.

images.name: Jadeveon Clowney [600x600]
images.caption: The Panthers added veteran Jadeveon Clowney during the offseason, but their outside linebacker corps remains thin.
